==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Provant
<hw>Pro*vant"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To supply with
provender or provisions; to provide for.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Nash.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Provant
<hw>Prov"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Provided for common
or general use, as in an army; hence, common in quality; inferior.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A poor <xex>provant</xex> rapier.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prove</ent>⟦br⟧
